  "prompt": "How do parents feel when their kid has depression?",
  "response": "When a child has depression, parents often experience a wide range of intense emotions. Here are some common feelings they may have:\n\n1. **Worry and Fear**: Parents may feel deeply concerned about their child\u2019s well-being, safety, and future. They may fear the long-term impact of depression on their child\u2019s life.\n\n2. **Helplessness**: Parents might feel powerless or unsure of how to help, especially if their child\u2019s depression doesn\u2019t respond immediately to treatment or support.\n\n3. **Guilt**: Some parents blame themselves, wondering if they did something wrong or missed signs of their child\u2019s struggle.\n\n4. **Sadness**: Seeing their child in pain can be heartbreaking, leading to feelings of profound sadness.\n\n5. **Frustration**: If parents feel unable to connect with their child or help them, they may experience frustration and even resentment at times.\n\n6. **Confusion**: Depression can be hard to understand, especially if the child\u2019s symptoms seem out of character or disproportionate to their life circumstances.\n\n7. **Overwhelm**: Managing their own emotions while trying to support their child can feel exhausting and overwhelming.\n\n8. **Hope**: Many parents hold onto hope, seeking professional help and believing their child can recover with appropriate treatment and support.\n\n9. **Isolation**: Parents may feel alone, especially if they don\u2019t have a support system or feel misunderstood by others who don\u2019t grasp the severity of their child\u2019s condition.\n\n10. **Determination**: Despite the challenges, many parents feel motivated to advocate for their child, seek resources, and provide unwavering support.\n\nIt\u2019s important for parents to also care for their own mental health during this time. Seeking therapy, joining support groups, and educating themselves about depression can help them better support their child while managing their own emotions.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
